  "text": "The fastest frequency (15 Hz), linked to early visual cortex responses [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , was likely to limit the extent of the representation within the face network. As such, we predicted that the 15 Hz signal would not yield any differences in the representation of familiar and unfamiliar faces. To the extent that any differences are observed, either in signal amplitude or using a multivariate analysis, these findings likely reflect low-level featural differences or perhaps differences in attention.",
